<div type="translation" source="bib:Gillet2024_01">

<p> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/> This is the [3]7th year of Kōpparakesarivarman who has taken Madurai. For Mahādeva of Tiruvālantuṟai in Ciṟupaḻuvūr, a <foreign>brahmadeya</foreign> of Kuṉṟakkūṟṟam, Maṇaṟkuṭi, a <foreign>kaṇattaṉ</foreign> (member of the assembly) of Muṉpālai in Miḻalaikkūṟṟam in Pāṇṭināṭu, to burn <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>eriya</foreign></supplied>, as long as the sun and the moon endure, gave <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vaitta</foreign></supplied> 90 undying and non-ageing <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>cāvāmūvā</foreign></supplied> great goats <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>perāṭu</foreign></supplied> for one <foreign>uḻakku</foreign> of <foreign>ghee</foreign> <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>neykku</foreign></supplied> by the <foreign>nārāyam</foreign> [measure] every day <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nicatam</foreign></supplied>. This is under the protection of the Panmāheśvaras.</p></div>

